Reasoning: The paper focuses on the development of a large-scale benchmark for autonomous driving, specifically for the tasks of dynamic tracking, interactive event recognition, and intention prediction. These tasks are closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO), as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in general. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of semantic segmentation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
